   <div class="view view-home-slideshow view-id-home_slideshow view-display-id-default view-dom-id-af18b89e203ccb47d3ce73fd2c6e54a4">
    <div class="view-content">
     <section class="rotation">
      <ul class="slides">
       <li class="slide active">
        <div class="image">
         <span class="field">
          <img alt="Catalyst Program Awards" src="https://nicholasinstitute.duke.edu/sites/default/files/slides/home-slider-catalyst-10-13-2.jpg"/>
         </span>
         <div class="slide-view-attribution">
          Image credit: Jessica Sheffield
         </div>
        </div>
        <article class="slide-view">
         <h3>
          Catalyst Program Proposals
         </h3>
         <p>
          March 15 is the final day to submit proposals for this year's Catalyst Program. The program invests in policy-relevant proposals that catalyze Nicholas Institute and faculty collaborations in new or emergent areas of shared interest.
         </p>
         <a class="more" href="https://nicholasinstitute.duke.edu/catalyst-program" target="_self">
          About the program
         </a>
        </article>
       </li>
       <li class="slide">
        <div class="image">
         <span class="field">
          <img alt="Duke University Energy Access Project, photo by Robyn Meeks" src="https://nicholasinstitute.duke.edu/sites/default/files/slides/home-slider-energy-access-project-0219.jpg"/>
         </span>
         <div class="slide-view-attribution">
          Image credit: Robyn Meeks
         </div>
        </div>
        <article class="slide-view">
         <h3>
          Energy Access Project
         </h3>
         <p>
          The Energy Access Project is developing solutions to energy policy and market challenges in emerging economies. Visit the new
          <a href="https://energyaccess.duke.edu/">
           project website
          </a>
          and
          <a href="https://nicholasinstitute.duke.edu/pages/social-media">
           follow us
          </a>
          for the latest work of Duke faculty and students tackling the energy access challenge.
         </p>
         <a class="more" href="https://energyaccess.duke.edu/" target="_blank">
          Learn all about the Energy Access Project
         </a>
        </article>
       </li>
       <li class="slide">
        <div class="image">
         <span class="field">
          <img alt="Deforestation Risks in China" src="https://nicholasinstitute.duke.edu/sites/default/files/slides/home-slider-china-deforestation-0119.jpg"/>
         </span>
         <div class="slide-view-attribution">
          Image credit: Vmenkov
         </div>
        </div>
        <article class="slide-view">
         <h3>
          Deforestation Risks along China’s New Silk Road
         </h3>
         <p>
          A new
          <a href="https://nicholasinstitute.duke.edu/articles/deforestation-risks-china%E2%80%99s-belt-and-road-initiative">
           blog post
          </a>
          at The Brookings Institution co-authored by Elizabeth Losos and Lydia Olander, based on their new
          <a href="https://nicholasinstitute.duke.edu/publications/reducing-environmental-risks-belt-and-road-initiative-investments-transportation-infrastructure">
           working paper
          </a>
          , provides a simple framework and illustrations of how one environmental risk from the overland (“belt”) part of the BRI might be assessed.
         </p>
         <a class="more" href="https://nicholasinstitute.duke.edu/articles/deforestation-risks-china%E2%80%99s-belt-and-road-initiative" target="_self">
          Read full story
         </a>
        </article>
       </li>
       <li class="slide">
        <div class="image">
         <span class="field">
          <img alt="Fish, photo by iStock.com/Global_Pics" src="https://nicholasinstitute.duke.edu/sites/default/files/slides/home-slider-fisheries-0119.jpg"/>
         </span>
         <div class="slide-view-attribution">
          Image credit: iStock.com/Global_Pics
         </div>
        </div>
        <article class="slide-view">
         <h3>
          2018 Fisheries Forum
         </h3>
         <p>
          The 2018 Forum convened by the Fisheries Leadership &amp; Sustainability Forum (Fisheries Forum) explored the role of learning, evaluation, and planning in the regional fishery management council process.
         </p>
         <a class="more" href="https://nicholasinstitute.duke.edu/publications/learning_evaluation_and_planning_fisheries_forum_2018" target="_self">
          See the proceedings
         </a>
        </article>
       </li>
       <li class="slide">
        <div class="image">
         <span class="field">
          <img alt="Jim Rogers" src="https://nicholasinstitute.duke.edu/sites/default/files/slides/home-slider-jim-rogers-121818.jpg"/>
         </span>
        </div>
        <article class="slide-view">
         <h3>
          On the Passing of Jim Rogers
         </h3>
         <p>
          The Nicholas Institute for Environmental Policy Solutions, and the larger Duke University community, are heartbroken at the loss of our good friend, Jim Rogers.
         </p>
         <a class="more" href="https://nicholasinstitute.duke.edu/articles/statement-passing-jim-rogers" target="_self">
          More about Jim
         </a>
        </article>
       </li>
      </ul>
